FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://1password.local

# 1Password Connect
REST API interface for 1Password Connect.

## Authentication
This API uses JSON Web Tokens for its authentication.

The parameters that are needed to be sent for this type of authentication are as follows:
+ `JWTHeaderName`
+ `JWTAcquireURL`
+ `JWTDestroyURL`

# Group Items

Access and manage items inside 1Password Vaults

## Vaults Items By VaultUuid [/vaults/{vaultUuid}/items{?filter}]

+ Parameters
    + vaultUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the Vault to fetch Items from


### GetVaultItems [GET]
+ Parameters
    + filter (string, optional)

        Filter the Item collection based on Item name using SCIM eq filter

        + Sample: title eq "Some Item Name"

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        OK

    + Attributes (array[Item])



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Invalid or missing token

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"Invalid token signature","status":401}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        Vault not found

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"vault {vaultUuid} not found","status":404}



## Vaults Items By VaultUuid [/vaults/{vaultUuid}/items]

+ Parameters
    + vaultUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the Vault to create an Item in


### CreateVaultItem [POST]

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (FullItem)



