### PatchVaultItem [PATCH]
Applies a modified [RFC6902 JSON Patch](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6902) document to an Item or ItemField. This endpoint only supports `add`, `remove` and `replace` operations.

When modifying a specific ItemField, the ItemField's ID in the `path` attribute of the operation object: `/fields/{fieldId}`

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (array[Patch])



+ Response 200 (application/json)

        OK - Item updated. If no Patch operations were provided, Item is unmodified.

    + Attributes (FullItem)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Invalid or missing token

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"Invalid token signature","status":401}


+ Response 403 (application/json)

        Unauthorized access

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"vault {vaultUuid} is not in scope","status":403}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        Item not found

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"item {itemUuid} not found","status":404}


### UpdateVaultItem [PUT]

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (FullItem)



