# Group Files

## Vaults Items Files By VaultUuid [/vaults/{vaultUuid}/items/{itemUuid}/files{?inline_files}]

+ Parameters
    + vaultUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the Vault to fetch Items from

    + itemUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the Item to fetch files from


### GetItemFiles [GET]
+ Parameters
    + inline_files (boolean, optional)

        Tells server to return the base64-encoded file contents in the response.

        + Sample: true

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        OK

    + Attributes (array[File])



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Invalid or missing token

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"Invalid token signature","status":401}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        Item not found

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"item {itemUuid} not found","status":404}


+ Response 413 (application/json)

        File content too large to display

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"File is too large to inline in request. Use the /v1/vaults/{vaultUUID}/items/{itemUUID}/files/{fileUUID}/content endpoint instead.","status":413}



## Vaults Items Files FileUuid By VaultUuid [/vaults/{vaultUuid}/items/{itemUuid}/files/{fileUuid}{?inline_files}]

+ Parameters
    + vaultUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the Vault to fetch Item from

    + itemUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the Item to fetch File from

    + fileUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the File to fetch


### GetDetailsOfFileById [GET]
+ Parameters
    + inline_files (boolean, optional)

        Tells server to return the base64-encoded file contents in the response.

        + Sample: true

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        OK

    + Attributes (File)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Invalid or missing token

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"Invalid token signature","status":401}


+ Response 403 (application/json)

        Unauthorized access

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"vault {vaultUuid} is not in scope","status":403}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        File not found

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"file {fileUuid} not found","status":404}


+ Response 413 (application/json)

        File content too large to display

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"File is too large to inline in request. Use the /v1/vaults/{vaultUUID}/items/{itemUUID}/files/{fileUUID}/content endpoint instead.","status":413}



## Vaults Items Files FileUuid Content [/vaults/{vaultUuid}/items/{itemUuid}/files/{fileUuid}/content]

+ Parameters
    + vaultUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the Vault the item is in

    + itemUuid (string, required)

        The UUID of the Item the File is in

    + fileUuid (string, required)

        UUID of the file to get content from


### DownloadFileByID [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/octet-stream)

        Success




+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Invalid or missing token

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"Invalid token signature","status":401}


+ Response 404 (application/json)

        File not found

    + Attributes (ErrorResponse)


    + Body

            {"message":"file {fileUuid} not found","status":404}




# Data Structures

## APIRequest (object)
Represents a request that was made to the API. Including what Token was used and what resource was accessed.

### Properties
+ `action` (enum[string], optional) 
    + `READ`
    + `CREATE`
    + `UPDATE`
    + `DELETE`
+ `actor` (Actor, optional) 
+ `requestId` (string, optional) - The unique id used to identify a single request.
+ `resource` (Resource, optional) 
+ `result` (enum[string], optional) 
    + `SUCCESS`
    + `DENY`
+ `timestamp` (string, optional) - The time at which the request was processed by the server.


## ErrorResponse (object)


### Properties
+ `message` (string, optional) - A message detailing the error
+ `status` (number, optional) - HTTP Status Code


## Field (object)


### Properties
+ `entropy` (number, optional) - For fields with a purpose of `PASSWORD` this is the entropy of the value
+ `generate`: `false` (boolean, optional) - If value is not present then a new value should be generated for this field
+ `id` (string, required) 
+ `label` (string, optional) 
+ `purpose` (enum[string], optional) - Some item types, Login and Password, have fields used for autofill. This property indicates that purpose and is required for some item types.
    + `USERNAME`
    + `PASSWORD`
    + `NOTES`
+ `recipe` (GeneratorRecipe, optional) - The recipe is used in conjunction with the "generate" property to set the character set used to generate a new secure value
+ `section` (Section, optional) 
+ `type` (enum[string], required) 
    + `STRING`
    + `EMAIL`
    + `CONCEALED`
    + `URL`
    + `TOTP`
    + `DATE`
    + `MONTH_YEAR`
    + `MENU`
+ `value` (string, optional) 


## File (object)


### Properties
+ `content` (string, optional) - Base64-encoded contents of the file. Only set if size <= OP_MAX_INLINE_FILE_SIZE_KB kb and `inline_files` is set to `true`.
+ `content_path` (string, optional) - Path of the Connect API that can be used to download the contents of this file.
+ `id` (string, optional) - ID of the file
+ `name` (string, optional) - Name of the file
+ `section` (Section1, optional) - For files that are in a section, this field describes the section.
+ `size` (number, optional) - Size in bytes of the file


## FullItem (object)


### Properties
+ `category` (enum[string], required) 
    + `LOGIN`
    + `PASSWORD`
    + `API_CREDENTIAL`
    + `SERVER`
    + `DATABASE`
    + `CREDIT_CARD`
    + `MEMBERSHIP`
    + `PASSPORT`
    + `SOFTWARE_LICENSE`
    + `OUTDOOR_LICENSE`
    + `SECURE_NOTE`
    + `WIRELESS_ROUTER`
    + `BANK_ACCOUNT`
    + `DRIVER_LICENSE`
    + `IDENTITY`
    + `REWARD_PROGRAM`
    + `DOCUMENT`
    + `EMAIL_ACCOUNT`
    + `SOCIAL_SECURITY_NUMBER`
    + `MEDICAL_RECORD`
    + `SSH_KEY`
    + `CUSTOM`
+ `createdAt` (string, optional) 
+ `favorite`: `false` (boolean, optional) 
+ `id` (string, optional) 
+ `lastEditedBy` (string, optional) 
+ `state` (enum[string], optional) 
    + `ARCHIVED`
    + `DELETED`
+ `tags` (array[string], optional) 
+ `title` (string, optional) 
+ `updatedAt` (string, optional) 
+ `urls` (array[Url], optional) 
+ `vault` (Vault1, required) 
+ `version` (number, optional) 
+ `fields` (array[Field], optional) 
+ `files` (array[File], optional) 
+ `sections` (array[Section2], optional) 


## GeneratorRecipe (object)
The recipe is used in conjunction with the "generate" property to set the character set used to generate a new secure value

### Properties
+ `characterSets` (array, optional) 
    + (enum[string])
        + Members
            + `LETTERS`
            + `DIGITS`
            + `SYMBOLS`
+ `excludeCharacters`: `abc1` (string, optional) - List of all characters that should be excluded from generated passwords.
+ `length`: `32` (number, optional) - Length of the generated value


## Item (object)


### Properties
+ `category` (enum[string], required) 
    + `LOGIN`
    + `PASSWORD`
    + `API_CREDENTIAL`
    + `SERVER`
    + `DATABASE`
    + `CREDIT_CARD`
    + `MEMBERSHIP`
    + `PASSPORT`
    + `SOFTWARE_LICENSE`
    + `OUTDOOR_LICENSE`
    + `SECURE_NOTE`
    + `WIRELESS_ROUTER`
    + `BANK_ACCOUNT`
    + `DRIVER_LICENSE`
    + `IDENTITY`
    + `REWARD_PROGRAM`
    + `DOCUMENT`
    + `EMAIL_ACCOUNT`
    + `SOCIAL_SECURITY_NUMBER`
    + `MEDICAL_RECORD`
    + `SSH_KEY`
    + `CUSTOM`
+ `createdAt` (string, optional) 
+ `favorite`: `false` (boolean, optional) 
+ `id` (string, optional) 
+ `lastEditedBy` (string, optional) 
+ `state` (enum[string], optional) 
    + `ARCHIVED`
    + `DELETED`
+ `tags` (array[string], optional) 
+ `title` (string, optional) 
+ `updatedAt` (string, optional) 
+ `urls` (array[Url], optional) 
+ `vault` (Vault1, required) 
+ `version` (number, optional) 


## ServiceDependency (object)
The state of a registered server dependency.

### Properties
+ `message` (string, optional) - Human-readable message for explaining the current state.
+ `service` (string, optional) 
+ `status` (string, optional) 


## Vault (object)


### Properties
+ `attributeVersion` (number, optional) - The vault version
+ `contentVersion` (number, optional) - The version of the vault contents
+ `createdAt` (string, optional) 
+ `description` (string, optional) 
+ `id` (string, optional) 
+ `items` (number, optional) - Number of active items in the vault
+ `name` (string, optional) 
+ `type` (enum[string], optional) 
    + `USER_CREATED`
    + `PERSONAL`
    + `EVERYONE`
    + `TRANSFER`
+ `updatedAt` (string, optional) 


## Actor (object)


### Properties
+ `account` (string, optional) 
+ `id` (string, optional) 
+ `jti` (string, optional) 
+ `requestIp` (string, optional) 
+ `userAgent` (string, optional) 


## Health Response (object)


### Properties
+ `dependencies` (array[ServiceDependency], optional) 
+ `name` (string, required) 
+ `version` (string, required) - The Connect server's version


## Item2 (object)


### Properties
+ `id` (string, optional) 


## Patch (object)


### Properties
+ `op` (enum[string], required) 
    + `add`
    + `remove`
    + `replace`
+ `path`: `/fields/06gnn2b95example10q91512p5/label` (string, required) - An RFC6901 JSON Pointer pointing to the Item document, an Item Attribute, and Item Field by Field ID, or an Item Field Attribute
+ `value` (object, optional) 


## Resource (object)


### Properties
+ `item` (Item2, optional) 
+ `itemVersion` (number, optional) 
+ `type` (enum[string], optional) 
    + `ITEM`
    + `VAULT`
+ `vault` (Vault3, optional) 


## Section (object)


### Properties
+ `id` (string, optional) 


## Section1 (object)
For files that are in a section, this field describes the section.

### Properties
+ `id` (string, optional) 


## Section2 (object)


### Properties
+ `id` (string, optional) 
+ `label` (string, optional) 


## Url (object)


### Properties
+ `href` (string, required) 
+ `label` (string, optional) 
+ `primary` (boolean, optional) 


## Vault1 (object)


### Properties
+ `id` (string, required) 


## Vault3 (object)


### Properties
+ `id` (string, optional) 

